i></ul></li><li class="index-3 nav-item dropdown"><a title='Information for HttF attendees' class='nav-link dropdown-toggle' href="#" role="button" data-toggle="dropdown" aria-haspopup="true" aria-expanded="false">Attendees</a><ul class="dropdown-menu glass" aria-labelledby="navbar"><li class="index-1 first"><a title='Venue' class='nav-link ' href="/2019/venue">Venue</a></li><li class="index-2"><a title='Hotel' class='nav-link ' href="/2019/hotel">Hotel</a></li><li class="index-3"><a title='Registration' class='nav-link ' href="/2019/registration">Registration</a></li><li class="index-4"><a title='SIGCHI Student Rate' class='nav-link ' href="/2019/sigchi-student-subsidy">SIGCHI Student Rate</a></li><li class="index-5"><a title='Code of Conduct' class='nav-link ' href="/2019/conduct">Code of Conduct</a></li><li class="index-6 last"><a title='Visas and Brexit' class='nav-link ' href="/2019/visas-and-brexit">Visas and Brexit</a></li></ul></li><li class="index-4 nav-item dropdown"><a title='Programme information for the symposium' class='nav-link dropdown-toggle' href="#" role="button" data-toggle="dropdown" aria-haspopup="true" aria-expanded="false">Programme</a><ul class="dropdown-menu glass" aria-labelledby="navbar"><li class="index-1 first"><a title='Programme' class='nav-link ' href="/2019/programme">Programme</a></li><li class="index-2"><a title='Keynote speakers' class='nav-link ' href="/2019/keynotes">Keynote speakers</a></li><li class="index-3"><a title='Symposium themes' class='nav-link ' href="/2019/themes">Symposium themes</a></li><li class="index-4 last"><a title='Feedback' class='nav-link ' href="/2019/feedback">Feedback</a></li></ul></li><li class="index-5 nav-item dropdown"><a title='Details about the organising committee and programme committee' class='nav-link dropdown-toggle' href="#" role="button" data-toggle="dropdown" aria-haspopup="true" aria-expanded="false">Organisers</a><ul class="dropdown-menu glass" aria-labelledby="navbar"><li class="index-1 first"><a title='Organising Committee' class='nav-link ' href="/2019/organising-committee">Organising Committee</a></li><li class="index-2 last"><a title='Programme Committee' class='nav-link ' href="/2019/programme-committee">Programme Committee</a></li></ul></li><li class="index-6 last"><a title='Details about sponsoring the symposium' class='nav-link ' href="/2019/sponsorship">Sponsors</a></li></ul><!--<form method="get" action="/2019/search" class="form-block nav-search"><input type="search" class="form-control nav-search-input pull-right" name="search" placeholder="Search…" value=""></form>--></nav></div></div></header><div class="row"><div class="main-container container-fluid"><div class="main row p-md-4 pt-sm-2 p-sm-1 pt-2 p-0 shadow"><div class="breadcrumb-container col-12"><nav aria-label="breadcrumb" class="shadow rounded"><ol class="breadcrumb"><li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/2019/">Halfway to the Future</a></li><li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/2019/programme">Programme</a></li><li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/2019/sessions/ubicomp">Ubiquitous Computing</a></li><li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">Future-looking paper</li></ol></nav></div><div class="col-xl-9 col-lg-8 col-md-7 col-12"><div class="jumbotron p-3 m-0 mb-3 rounded shadow"><h1>Social AI for Engaging UbiComp</h1><p>Alessio Antonini <em><small>(Knowledge Media Institute, The Open University, UK)</small></em><br> Lucia Lupi <em><small>(DIST, Polytechnic of Turin, Italy and University of Turin, Italy)</small></em></p></div><article><div class="px-3"><p>This short paper introduces the concept of Social AI as pivot technology between the two visions of Weiser's “calm” and Rogers's “engaging” UbiComp technologies. We discuss three types of AI solutions, Personal AI, System AI and Social AI, in relation to their interaction with ubiquitous technologies and humans. We highlight as Personal and System AI are the perfect users of calm technologies, while Social AI instantiates the vision of engaging Ubicomp. We elaborate the concept of Social AI as a technology for navigating the dual complexity of social systems and operating in synergy with humans without eroding their agency and by seeking their support through communication. We conclude by envisioning an entangled future between the research agenda on Social AI and engaging Ubicomp.</p></div><div class="card shadow rounded" class="p-2"><div class="card-body"><h5 class="card-title">Citation</h5><p class="card-text"> Alessio Antonini and Lucia Lupi. 2019. Social AI for Engaging UbiComp. In <em>Proceedings of the Halfway to the Future Symposium 2019 (HTTF 2019), November 19–20, 2019, Nottingham, United Kingdom</em>. ACM, New York, NY, USA, 5 pages. <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3363384.3363483" title="DOI for the article &#039;Social AI for Engaging UbiComp&#039;">https://doi.org/10.1145/3363384.3363483</a></p></div></div></article></div><aside class="col-xl-3 col-lg-4 col-md-5 col-12"><div class="card shadow rounded" class="p-2"><div class="card-body"><div class="media event-details mb-3"><i class="fas fa-presentation mr-2 event-details-icon" title="This is a future-looking paper given as a presentation" aria-label="This is a future-looking paper given as a presentation"></i><div class="media-body">Future-looking paper, given as a <strong>presentation</strong></div></div><div class="media event-details"><i class="fas fa-location-circle mr-2 event-details-icon" title="Location of the " aria-label="Location of the "></i><div class="media-body"> The Great Hall </div></div><hr><div class="media event-details mb-3"><i class="fas fa-calendar-day mr-2 event-details-icon" title="Date of the future-looking paper"aria-label="Date of the future-looking paper"></i><div class="media-body"><strong>Wed. 20th November</strong></div></div><div class="media event-details mb-3"><i class="fas fa-clock mr-2 event-details-icon" title="Approximate start time of the future-looking paper" aria-label="Approximate start time of the future-looking paper"></i><div class="media-body">Starts at <strong>10:15</strong> approx.</div></div><div class="media event-details "><i class="fas fa-hourglass-end mr-2 event-details-icon" title="Length of the future-looking paper" aria-label="Length of the future-looking paper"></i><div class="media-body"><strong>5</strong> minutes long</div></div><hr><div class="media event-details mb-0"><i class="fas fa-link mr-2 event-details-icon" title="Browse the entry in the ACM Digital Library" aria-label="Browse the entry in the ACM Digital Library"></i><div class="media-body"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3363384.3363483" title="Browse the entry in the ACM Digital Library">ACM Digital Library</a></div></div></div></div><div class="card shadow rounded" class="p-2"><div class="card-body"><h5 class="card-title">Author keywords</h5><p>social AI, engaging ubicomp, calm technology, human-AI interaction</p></div></div></aside><div class="col-12 sponsors light"><p><strong>With thanks to our sponsors:</strong></p><p><a href="https://www.nottingham.ac.uk/" title="University of Nottingham"><img src="/2019/files/2019-06/partner-uon-black.png" alt="University of Nottingham logo" /></a></p><p><a href="https://sigchi.org/" title="ACM SIGCHI"><img src="/2019/files/2019-06/sponsor-sigchi-black.png" alt="SIGCHI logo" /></a></p><p><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/" title="Microsoft Research"><img src="/2019/files/2019-10/sponsor-microsoft-black.png" alt="Microsoft logo" /></a></p></div><div class="col-12 sponsors dark"><p><strong>With thanks to our sponsors:</strong></p><p><a href="https://www.nottingham.ac.uk/" title="University of Nottingham"><img src="/2019/files/2019-06/partner-uon-white.png" alt="University of Nottingham logo" /></a></p><p><a href="https://sigchi.org/" title="ACM SIGCHI"><img src="/2019/files/2019-06/sponsor-sigchi-white.png" alt="SIGCHI logo" /></a></p><p><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/" title="Microsoft Research"><img src="/2019/files/2019-10/sponsor-microsoft-white.png" alt="Microsoft logo" /></a></p></div></div></div></div></div><footer class="container"><div class="row"><div class="footer-container container-fluid"><div class="row d-flex flex-column justify-content-center flex-md-row"><p>© Halfway to the Future 2019.</p><p>Read our <a href="/2019/privacy-policy" title="HttF Privacy Policy">Privacy Policy</a>.</p><p>Follow us on <a href="https://twitter.com/httfsymposium" title="@httfsymposium on Twitter">Twitter</a>.</p><hr><p>Designed by <a href="https://www.porcheron.uk/" title="Martin Porcheron">Martin Porcheron</a>.</p></div></div></div></footer></body></html>